For Homeowners







Search:








Home
Homeowners
Renovation




 Getting ready to upgrade or renovate your home?
Click the areas of the home to learn about projects you can do to make your home more comfortable and energy efficient.

Attics Attics
Attic insulation is essential for keeping out cold air in the winter and hot air in the summer. Insulating your attic is a DIY project you can do in a weekend, and it can save you up to 20% on your energy bills.

Floors & Walls Floors & Walls
Adding insulation to floors and walls will help improve noise control in your home as well as thermal performance. So you can enjoy a quieter, more comfortable home.

Duct Insulation Duct Insulation
Duct insulation keeps heated and cooled air flowing to the farthest reaches of your home, while it helps stop unwanted sounds from spreading.

Basements/Crawlspaces Basements/Crawlspaces
Basements and crawlspaces need the right insulation to manage exposure to moisture, minimize energy costs, and maximize your home's living space. Owens Corning has everything you need to properly insulate below grade.

Specialty Projects Specialty Projects
See how easy it is to add comfort and savings throughout your home with our specialty products.

See All ProjectsSee All Projects
See an overview of all the insulation projects you might consider when renovating your home, along with a list of the relevant Owens-Corning products. The products are arranged by the relevant projects, all on the same page.


Insulation Comfort 
Take our Home Insulation Comfort Quiz to find the sources of energy loss in your home and what you can do to fix problems.
EcoTouch® Insulation Featuredon Ask This Old House 
Watch as an installation contractor shows techniques on installing insulation the right way.See the video now!










